name: WooCommerce
description: Add a WooCommerce Instance to connect your existing WooCommerce account to the eCommerce Hub, allowing you to manage orders and products across multiple eCommerce Elements. You will need your WooCommerce API information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Max Page Size (or limit)
configuration.description: WooCommerce Beta Max Page Size (or limit)

configuration.name: Event Notification Instance Finder
configuration.description: WooCommerce Beta Event Notification Instance Finder

configuration.name: The Store URL
configuration.description: The base URL for your specific WooCommerce store.

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Parameter Authentication
configuration.description: Indicates whether to use parameters for authentication of HTTPS

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: WooCommerce Beta Event Notification Callback URL

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Find all customers in the eCommerce system.
Find all customers in the eCommerce system.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. When this parameter is omitted, 1 is implied.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for objects where name equals foo, the search expression will be name='foo'. When this parameter is omitted, all objects are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to fetch in a given page. When this parameter is omitted, 200 results are returned.

parameters.name: returnTotalCount
parameters.description: Optionally return the total amount of customers.
